        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:01PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 701 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Union, or near Whitmire, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuckertown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
